# AI Blog Generator: User Input Framework

> What data to collect from users to generate the best SEO-optimized content.

---

## Input Categories Overview

```
1. Brand Context       → Who they are (one-time setup)
2. Target Audience     → Who they're writing for
3. Content Generation  → What to create
4. SEO Inputs          → Optimization specifics
5. E-E-A-T Signals     → Human authenticity
6. Linking Strategy    → Internal + external links
7. Technical SEO       → Schema, meta, structure
8. Media & Output      → Format, images, publishing
```

---

## 1. BRAND CONTEXT (Setup once, reuse)

| Input | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| Company name | Brand mentions |
| Website URL | Analyze voice, find internal links |
| Industry/Niche | Terminology, context |
| Brand voice | "Professional", "Casual expert", etc. |
| Sample content URL | Learn their style |
| Competitors (URLs) | Outrank analysis |
| Unique selling points | Differentiation |

---

## 2. TARGET AUDIENCE

| Input | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| Reader type | B2B/B2C, job titles |
| Expertise level | Beginner / Intermediate / Expert |
| Pain points | Problems to address |
| Search intent | Informational / Commercial / Transactional |
| Geographic target | Local SEO, language |

---

## 3. CONTENT GENERATION

| Input | Options |
|-------|---------|
| Quantity | Number of articles |
| Topics | General (all) + Specific (per article) |
| Article type | How-to, Listicle, Comparison, Review, Opinion, Case study |
| Word count | Per article or bulk default (500-5000+) |
| Tone preset | Conversational, Professional, Academic, Sales-focused |
| Structure | Minimal / Standard / Detailed headings |

---

## 4. SEO INPUTS

| Input | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| Primary keyword | Main ranking target (1 per article) |
| Secondary keywords | Supporting keywords (3-5 per article) |
| Target search intent | Informational / Commercial / Transactional |
| Featured snippet target | Structure for position 0 |
| People Also Ask | Specific questions to answer |
| Competitor URL to outrank | Analyze and beat |

---

## 5. E-E-A-T SIGNALS (Human authenticity)

| Input | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| Author name | Byline, expertise signal |
| Author bio/credentials | "10 years experience", certifications |
| First-hand experience | "We tested...", "Our data shows..." |
| Original data/stats | Unique research to include |
| Testimonials/quotes | Social proof |

---

## 6. LINKING STRATEGY

| Input | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| Internal links | Pages on their site to link to |
| Pillar page URL | Main page for topic cluster |
| External sources | Specific URLs or "auto-find" |
| Products to mention | Natural product placement |
| CTA destination | Where to send readers |

---

## 7. TECHNICAL SEO

| Input | Options |
|-------|---------|
| Schema type | Article, HowTo, FAQ, Review, Product |
| Include FAQ section | Yes / No |
| Include TOC | Yes / No (for long articles) |
